content.description:
Unique boulder on a wooden pillar with plastic holds.

 Start with hands on the waist-high green and red hold. Shoot up to the red shell and then mantle to the top. Take a minute to enjoy the view at the top before either jumping off or climbing down.
content.location:
East of Ocean and 20th. You should be able to see the large wooden pillars from the most southern end of the Belmar boardwalk

 There are three pillars, this climb is on the pillar in the middle of the three. Potential for the climb to be inaccessible due to water if high tide.

content.description:
Beach area, very crowded in the busy season (summer). Main climbing includes two large wood pillars with climbing holds. You may need a beach pass in the summer.

 The middle pillar has been climbed, however the most southern pillar is still unclimbed, climbing shoes are likely needed to send the most southern pillar.Â
